Ansible roles - available in ansible roles 
it helps to organize the playbooks and break them into smaller parts.

- lot of variables
- lot of parameters
- lot of secrets
- management of all this in a single playbook becomes a headache to manage

-> Use Ansible Galaxy - ansible-galaxy role init kubernetes
  
  role - gives us many folders to structure our playbook well

  - meta - meta defines the metadata about the purpose of the role and the playbook
  - defaults - to store the default variables for the store
  - vars - to declare the variables
  - group-vars
  - tasks 
  - handlers - handling some kind of exceptions
  - files - to pass the files to the tasks - to other machine
  - templates - jinja2 templating